Ghana, Ivory Coast Sign UNHCR Deal on Refugees, Graphic Reports

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-10-07T09:51:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/ghana-ivory-coast-sign-unhcr-deal-on-refugees-graphic-reports.html
Ghana ,  Ivory Coast  and the United
Nations High Commission for Refugees have signed an agreement to
repatriate 18,000 Ivorian refugees in Ghana, the  Daily Graphic 
reported.  The two countries have also agreed to jointly engage the
UNHCR to repatriate Ivorian refugees identified as ex-combatants
to a country that doesn’t share a border with Ivory Coast, the
Accra-based newspaper said.  The agreement was signed by Mohammed Mumuni, Ghana’s
foreign minister, his Ivorian counterpart, Daniel Kablan Duncan,
and the country director for the UNHCR, Sharon Cooper, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
